of Bharata, the Yak<218>ag<193>na has attained a strong local colour. ç
The artists not only dance vigorously but also sing and talk according ç
to the roles they have to play. There is enough scope to show their ç
talents through impromptu speeches also. The stories and themes are ç
taken mostly from the epics and the pur<193><207>as.
At the background is the master who narrates the story and also sings ç
to the accompaniment of simple musical instruments. Now-a-days use ç
